The paper introduces an algorithm that learns a similarity matrix from crowdsourced data alone, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm uses adaptive sampling and triplet-based queries, which are common techniques in human-computer interaction and crowdsourcing (cs.HC, cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of SVMs to evaluate the crowd kernel, which is a common machine learning technique for classification and regression tasks (cs.MM).
